text: Latoya 'the Sheriff' Blackwood (born August 19, 1985) is a Canadian rugby union player. She represented at the 2014 Women's Rugby World Cup. She made her debut at the 2013 Nations Cup and retired in 2018.https://rugby.ca/en/news/2018/03/latoya-blackwood-has-confirmed-her- retirement-from-international-rugby She studied at Concordia University for a year where she was named as the fittest athlete in 2011-2012. ==References== ==External links== * Rugby Canada Player Profile Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Montreal Category:Canadian female rugby union players Category:Female rugby union players Category:Black Canadian sportspeople
